wpt.desc: Keeping Up With the Joneses by elora_c, Traditional Cache (2/2)

groundspeak:cache.groundspeak:name: Keeping Up With the Joneses
groundspeak:cache.groundspeak:short_description: A regular cache located off the Uwchlan Trail near the Jones Pond Pavilion.
groundspeak:cache.groundspeak:long_description:
The first caches we found were along the Struble and Uwchlan Trails, and these remain our favorite types. So when it came time to hide our first cache, we had to try to keep up with the hides around the area.

The Uwchlan Trail originates at the Struble Trail and wanders along Shamona Creek adjacent to Dowlin Forge Road. There are several parking areas along the two trails.

Jones Pond is a small park located on Dowlin Forge Road. It has a pavilion and a gazebo, both of which have benches overlooking Jones Pond. The park is open dawn to dusk.

The cache is a lock-and-lock type box located within 100 feet of the trail. The cache is placed with permission by Uwchlan Township.
